title: Breitbart News Daily: Texas Shootout, Sen. Sessions, and Super Tuesday
title_page: Breitbart News Daily: Texas Shootout, Sen. Sessions, and Super Tuesday | Breitbart
text:
On the February 26, Breitbart News Daily show, broadcast on Sirius XM Patriot channel 125 from 6AM to 9AM EST weekdays, host and Breitbart News executive chairman Stephen K. Bannon will discuss the Republican debate in Houston, Texas, and the state of the presidential primary race going into Super Tuesday.
Bannon will also have an important interview with Sen. Jeff Session (R-AL) on the issues of trade and immigration — both topics of critical importance in the 2016 presidential race.
Former Senator John Sununu will call in to discuss Ohio Gov. John Kasich’s presidential run, the GOP debate, and Super Tuesday.
Columnist Red Jahncke of the the New York Sun will speak about how Trump will likely lock up the Republican presidential nomination if he wins the Florida primary.
War correspondent Michael Yon will be interviewed about the rise of China as a military power.
Donald Trump’s campaign manager Corey Lewandowski will talk about Trump’s campaign and the Houston debate.
Polling Company President and CEO Kellyanne Conway, who runs a Ted Cruz-aligned SuperPAC, will come on the show to talk about the Cruz candidacy and the state of the race.
Joshua Green from Bloomberg will be interviewed about the GOP debate and the run-up to Super Tuesday.
Breitbart Texas corespondents will also be calling into the show to discuss the state of the race in Texas.
Breitbart News Daily is the first live, conservative radio enterprise to air seven days a week. Sirius XM Vice President for news and talk Dave Gorab called the show “the conservative news show of record.”
Follow Breitbart News on Twitter for live updates during the show. Listeners may call into the show at: 866-957-2874
